your-- oh, you have a question.

00:58:30.899 --> 00:58:32.190
AUDIENCE: Thank you for coming.

00:58:32.190 --> 00:58:35.330
And you started your talk
about-- you mentioned

00:58:35.330 --> 00:58:38.550
some fine lines when
you take a picture

00:58:38.550 --> 00:58:41.660
or sometimes you decide
not to take it, step away.

00:58:41.660 --> 00:58:44.190
You decide to publish
it or not to publish,

00:58:44.190 --> 00:58:47.360
to post-process and how
much to post-process.

00:58:47.360 --> 00:58:50.090
In your 40-plus
years experience,

00:58:50.090 --> 00:58:52.570
do those lines change?

00:58:52.570 --> 00:58:56.030
Do you regret today not
taking certain pictures

00:58:56.030 --> 00:58:59.210
or the opposite-- maybe you
published certain pictures that

00:58:59.210 --> 00:59:01.250
you today wouldn't?

00:59:01.250 --> 00:59:04.370
How much would you
change if anything?

00:59:04.370 --> 00:59:06.620
And maybe a related
question is, do you

00:59:06.620 --> 00:59:09.600
have any unpublished
pictures and why?

00:59:09.600 --> 00:59:12.059
Why wouldn't you
